        <headline>Heat Advisory issued June 26 at 2:58AM EDT until June 26 at 8:00PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Heat index values from 105 to 108 degrees expected.

* WHERE...Cabarrus, Davie, Iredell, Mecklenburg, Rowan, and Union
Counties.

* WHEN...From 2 PM this afternoon to 8 PM EDT this evening.

* IMPACTS...Hot temperatures and high humidity may cause heat
illnesses.
</description>
        <instruction>To reduce risk during outdoor work, the Occupational Safety and
Health Administration recommends scheduling frequent rest breaks in
shaded or air conditioned environments. Anyone overcome by heat
should be moved to a cool and shaded location. Heat stroke is an
emergency! Call 9 1 1.

Do not leave young children and pets in unattended vehicles. Car
interiors will reach lethal temperatures in a matter of minutes.

Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.</instruction>
